Known bugs and fragile areas.

- xsan golden test has rare BUS crashes (~2% rate) in JIT-generated code.
  Only under the triple sanitizer combination (address+integer+undefined).
  Does not reproduce in host, asan-only, or coverage-only builds.
  Likely a sanitizer-toolchain interaction with MAP_JIT, not a program bug.

- JIT rect dispatch only supports l=0 (horizontal stripes).  Column-based
  tiling (l>0) would need the inner loop separated from the stride.  The
  interpreter handles arbitrary rects already.

